<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 01:26:20 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>日本找到了 1200 年樱花数据的新管家，维持气候变化研究项目</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-japan-a-new-steward-for-1200-years-of-cherry-blossom-data-has-been-found-sustaining-a-climate-change-research-project-180988607/</link><description>去年夏天去世的气候科学家青野康幸学会了阅读古代日本文字，以汇编可追溯到公元九世纪的盛花期记录</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 20:56:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-japan-a-new-steward-for-1200-years-of-cherry-blossom-data-has-been-found-sustaining-a-climate-change-research-project-180988607/</guid></item><item><title>火星探测器发现了这颗红色星球上前所未见的生命基石，为古代宜居性提供了证据</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-mars-rover-found-building-blocks-of-life-never-seen-on-the-red-planet-before-boosting-the-case-for-ancient-habitability-180988610/</link><description>美国宇航局好奇号探测器发现的有机分子可能是由生命形成的，但它们也可能来自地质过程或陨石</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 20:10:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-mars-rover-found-building-blocks-of-life-never-seen-on-the-red-planet-before-boosting-the-case-for-ancient-habitability-180988610/</guid></item><item><title>直布罗陀著名的猴子正在吃泥土，可能会缓解因咀嚼游客垃圾食品而引起的胃痛</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gibraltars-famous-monkeys-are-eating-dirt-likely-to-alleviate-stomach-aches-from-munching-on-tourists-junk-food-180988606/</link><description>英国境内的巴巴里猕猴是欧洲唯一的野生猴子。但许多人正在食用热量、糖、盐和乳制品含量高、纤维含量低的人类零食</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 19:51:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/gibraltars-famous-monkeys-are-eating-dirt-likely-to-alleviate-stomach-aches-from-munching-on-tourists-junk-food-180988606/</guid></item><item><title>十年来首次在洪都拉斯山脉发现罕见的“云美洲虎”，代表环保主义者的胜利</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-rare-cloud-jaguar-was-spotted-in-honduran-mountains-for-the-first-time-in-a-decade-representing-a-win-for-conservationists-180988595/</link><description>这种大型猫科动物很少出现在高海拔地区，因此这一目击事件表明保护该地区野生动物走廊的努力正在发挥作用</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 15:37:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-rare-cloud-jaguar-was-spotted-in-honduran-mountains-for-the-first-time-in-a-decade-representing-a-win-for-conservationists-180988595/</guid></item><item><title>考古学家在 1,600 年前的埃及木乃伊包裹物中挖掘出《伊利亚特》的纸莎草碎片</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/archaeologists-unearth-a-papyrus-fragment-from-the-iliad-tucked-inside-the-wrappings-of-a-1600-year-old-egyptian-mummy-180988603/</link><description>荷马史诗的摘录以他的船只目录为特色，这是一段著名的段落，列出了航行到特洛伊的希腊军队。这可能是在木乃伊化背景下发现的第一个希腊文学文本</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 15:07:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/archaeologists-unearth-a-papyrus-fragment-from-the-iliad-tucked-inside-the-wrappings-of-a-1600-year-old-egyptian-mummy-180988603/</guid></item><item><title>可卡因污染似乎使鲑鱼比平常游得更快更远。科学家们不知道长期后果</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cocaine-pollution-seems-to-make-salmon-swim-faster-and-farther-than-usual-scientists-dont-know-the-long-term-consequences-180988600/</link><description>这种非法药物的主要副产品苯甲酰爱康宁比可卡因本身产生更强烈的影响。废水处理厂通常不会完全处理此类代谢物，因此它们在水体中的浓度经常高于其母体药物</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cocaine-pollution-seems-to-make-salmon-swim-faster-and-farther-than-usual-scientists-dont-know-the-long-term-consequences-180988600/</guid></item><item><title>50 年前，一对来自墨西哥的夫妇成为洛杉矶软塔可的先驱。现在，他们的餐厅已成为地标</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-couple-from-mexico-became-soft-taco-pioneers-in-los-angeles-50-years-ago-now-their-restaurant-is-a-landmark-180988602/</link><description>劳尔 (Raúl) 和卢佩·马丁内斯 (Lupe Martinez) 打开 King Taco，端上软玉米饼，就像他们在家乡记忆中一样。由于洛杉矶市议会的投票，剩下的事情现在已经正式成为历史</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 13:26:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-couple-from-mexico-became-soft-taco-pioneers-in-los-angeles-50-years-ago-now-their-restaurant-is-a-landmark-180988602/</guid></item><item><title>国家美术馆接受了借阅图书馆的新角色，感谢向其他博物馆发送艺术品的大礼</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-national-gallery-of-art-embraces-new-role-as-lending-library-thanks-to-a-big-gift-that-sends-artwork-to-other-museums-180988597/</link><description>长期受托人米切尔·P·拉尔斯 (Mitchell P. Rales) 的家族基金会捐赠 1.16 亿美元，用于分享博物馆的藏品，以纪念美国 250 岁生日</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 21:03:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-national-gallery-of-art-embraces-new-role-as-lending-library-thanks-to-a-big-gift-that-sends-artwork-to-other-museums-180988597/</guid></item><item><title>仿人机器人在中国比赛中打破了人类最快半程马拉松世界纪录</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-humanoid-robot-just-beat-the-human-world-record-for-the-fastest-half-marathon-during-a-race-in-china-180988599/</link><description>由中国电子公司荣耀开发的名为Lightning的自动导航机器人赢得了13.1英里的比赛。其成绩和其他成绩标志着自去年首届赛事以来取得的重大进步，当时 21 名机器人中只有 6 人到达了终点线</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 19:27:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-humanoid-robot-just-beat-the-human-world-record-for-the-fastest-half-marathon-during-a-race-in-china-180988599/</guid></item><item><title>旧金山的稀有硬币寻宝游戏为参与者提供了重温加州淘金热的机会</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-rare-coin-scavenger-hunt-in-san-francisco-offers-participants-the-chance-to-relive-the-california-gold-rush-180988598/</link><description>当地硬币经销商将在 4 月 25 日举行的第三届年度全市挑战赛中隐藏价值总计 50,000 美元的历史货币</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 18:42:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-rare-coin-scavenger-hunt-in-san-francisco-offers-participants-the-chance-to-relive-the-california-gold-rush-180988598/</guid></item><item><title>人类仍在进化。一项研究表明，自然选择青睐与红头发和较少男性型秃发有关的基因</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humans-are-still-evolving-natural-selection-has-favored-genes-linked-to-red-hair-and-less-male-pattern-baldness-a-study-suggests-180988563/</link><description>对数千名西欧亚人的古代和现代 DNA 进行的大规模研究发现了近 500 种近代历史上进化选择支持或反对的遗传变异</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 17:34:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humans-are-still-evolving-natural-selection-has-favored-genes-linked-to-red-hair-and-less-male-pattern-baldness-a-study-suggests-180988563/</guid></item><item><title>半个多世纪后，鲍勃·迪伦的《我不在那里》的原始打字稿歌词被重新发现</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bob-dylans-original-typewritten-draft-lyrics-for-im-not-there-have-been-rediscovered-after-more-than-half-a-century-180988592/</link><description>几十年来，热心的歌迷只能在盗版黑胶唱片上听到这首晦涩难懂的歌曲。歌词草稿位于艾伦·金斯伯格 (Allen Ginsberg) 诗歌的第一版副本中，刚刚在拍卖会上以 6,800 美元的价格售出</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 16:15:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bob-dylans-original-typewritten-draft-lyrics-for-im-not-there-have-been-rediscovered-after-more-than-half-a-century-180988592/</guid></item><item><title>一项研究表明，我们使用许多相同的脑细胞来观察和想象物体。这些发现为了解记忆提供了一个新窗口</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/we-use-many-of-the-same-brain-cells-to-see-and-to-imagine-objects-a-study-suggests-the-findings-provide-a-new-window-into-memory-180988580/</link><description>虽然过去的研究暗示相关大脑区域存在重叠，但新的研究深入到了细胞水平。这一发现可能有助于改善记忆障碍（如痴呆症）和某些精神疾病（如精神分裂症）的治疗</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/we-use-many-of-the-same-brain-cells-to-see-and-to-imagine-objects-a-study-suggests-the-findings-provide-a-new-window-into-memory-180988580/</guid></item><item><title>这个令人眼花缭乱的蒂芙尼彩色玻璃窗装饰了一座教堂一个多世纪。现在它需要一个新家</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-dazzling-tiffany-stained-glass-window-adorned-a-church-for-more-than-a-century-now-it-needs-a-new-home-180988590/</link><description>康涅狄格州温斯特德第二公理会教堂将拍卖以令人惊叹的瀑布和日落为特色的色彩缤纷的艺术品</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-dazzling-tiffany-stained-glass-window-adorned-a-church-for-more-than-a-century-now-it-needs-a-new-home-180988590/</guid></item><item><title>纽约市公墓修复了一座维多利亚时期的温室，欢迎游客来到其历史悠久的土地</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/green-wood-cemetery-restored-a-victorian-greenhouse-to-welcome-visitors-to-its-historic-grounds-180988588/</link><description>布鲁克林的格林伍德公墓源于 19 世纪的“乡村公墓”运动，该运动将墓地从狭窄、黑暗变成了广阔而美丽</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 20:35:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/green-wood-cemetery-restored-a-victorian-greenhouse-to-welcome-visitors-to-its-historic-grounds-180988588/</guid></item><item><title>宇航员对地球引力的记忆可能会影响他们移动和握住物体的方式，即使在太空中呆了几个月后也是如此</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronauts-memories-of-earths-gravity-may-influence-how-they-move-and-hold-objects-even-after-months-in-space-180988586/</link><description>科学家表示，检查太空旅行者的精细运动技能有助于提高未来任务的安全性</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 20:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronauts-memories-of-earths-gravity-may-influence-how-they-move-and-hold-objects-even-after-months-in-space-180988586/</guid></item><item><title>一位诗人的爱情故事被缩短后，他的信件神秘消失——直到珍本书经销商凭预感采取行动</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-john-keats-love-story-was-cut-short-his-letters-mysteriously-disappeared-until-rare-book-dealers-acted-on-a-hunch-180988585/</link><description>约翰济慈在英年早逝之前写给未婚妻的八封信是“一生的文学发现”</description><pubDate>Tue, 